  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to have an ability to completely disable communication in group chats created by me\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Group chat admin after leaving the chat still receives new messages in it\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nGroup chat is disabled and it's not possible to send new messages by it's members after admin left\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUser A (group chat admin) receives new message after leaving it\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices\r\n- Create 2 accounts \r\n- As user A add user B as a contact\r\n- As user A create a group chat with user B as a member\r\n- As user A (group chat admin) leave the group chat (Chat options -> Leave group chat -> Leave)\r\n- As user B send a message to the group chat\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- Change 'Leave group chat' option for something like 'Disable group chat' for it's admin\r\n- Make further communications impossible in a group chat after its admin disabled it\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: will be in develop after #3842 is merged\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n",
